Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.92,0:00:08.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the best I could do right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.59,0:00:13.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did this have to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.02,0:00:21.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rune information particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.89,0:00:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that they are your food?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.15,0:00:27.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are full of Runes! \NMemories, the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.63,0:00:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And life!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.19,0:00:31.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Which means, once you've \Ndevoured their memories,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.35,0:00:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you move on to the information \Nthat is their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.45,0:00:35.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What does he mean, food?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.74,0:00:38.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did Marie have to \Ndie because of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.83,0:00:42.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not me. It was the \NValvrave that killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.91,0:00:44.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.33,0:00:47.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The ones to blame are the \Nhumans who sealed me in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.84,0:00:49.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So they could use Runes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.61,0:00:50.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.51,0:00:53.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, JIORan scientists \Nturned you into an engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:00:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Through you, the Valvrave \Ncollects and uses Runes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.35,0:01:00.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes! That's why it's not my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.10,0:01:04.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do eat a little, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.44,0:01:06.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What she's saying is probably true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.27,0:01:07.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.61,0:01:11.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Marie's postmortem showed an \Nextremely low concentration
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.15,0:01:14.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of kynurenic acid in her brain \Nand red blood cells in her blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.03,0:01:16.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Far too low for someone who was \Nhealthy immediately beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.41,0:01:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably evidence that \Nher Runes had been eaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.70,0:01:23.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Tokishima.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.04,0:01:24.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your physical exams show the same
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.53,0:01:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,symptoms as Marie, although \Nmuch less pronounced.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.88,0:01:28.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.92,0:01:33.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you go on piloting the Valvrave, \Nyou'll end up just like Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.80,0:01:34.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An empty husk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.96,0:03:34.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Am I in the right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.42,0:03:36.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.21,0:03:39.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Me? I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:41.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.22,0:03:43.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.24,0:03:45.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You there! Mystery man!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:47.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.39,0:03:48.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.37,0:03:49.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.14,0:03:55.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto... Oh, right, I'm Haruto.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.82,0:03:57.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.94,0:04:01.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto... Haruto...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.66,0:04:04.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who's Haruto?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.66,0:04:05.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.12,0:04:16.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Get back! Stay away from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.25,0:04:19.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who am I?! What are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:35.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tokishima! Tokishima!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.71,0:04:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's an alert, so please \Nlaunch in your Valvrave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:41.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Valvrave...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.90,0:04:44.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unit 5 goes first! Got that, Haruto?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.09,0:05:07.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Hey! Haruto!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.26,0:05:10.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.93,0:05:11.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.98,0:05:13.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you okay? Can you stand?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.81,0:05:15.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.85,0:05:18.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Stand aside! I'm going first!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.11,0:05:19.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no need.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:19.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.96,0:05:21.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we have incoming enemies!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:22.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We don't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.15,0:05:25.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who sounded the false alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.45,0:05:27.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Before the operation, I needed \Nto ascertain whether or
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not our weapons were \Nfunctioning properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.24,0:05:33.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That jerk was testing me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.62,0:05:38.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are entering into a temporary \Npartnership with the Dorssian Royalists.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.75,0:05:40.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dorssian Royalists?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.17,0:05:43.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They want the royalty-based political \Nsystem that existed before the coup.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.97,0:05:45.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Put simply, an anti-government \Norganization.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.05,0:05:49.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They offered to provide us \Nwith supplies, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.39,0:05:52.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they want to work with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.93,0:05:54.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.51,0:05:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Royalists need our help \Nas much as we need theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.56,0:06:01.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Dorssian submarine \Nknown as "The Phantom."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.78,0:06:06.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Their condition for giving us \Nsupplies is that we destroy this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.45,0:06:07.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We scratch their back, \Nthey scratch ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.57,0:06:12.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The operation is set to \Ncommence in 32 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will tell everyone their work \Nassignments one hour from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.33,0:06:16.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An operation, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.54,0:06:17.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:20.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't looking for \NMiss Rukino come first?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.59,0:06:23.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's still missing, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.56,0:06:29.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Remember this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.05,0:06:33.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The most important thing for a \Nsoldier is to come home alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.56,0:06:34.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.14,0:06:36.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing to be concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.85,0:06:40.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to your life, this is trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.94,0:06:44.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He saved my life? Back \Nduring the cave-in?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.12,0:06:56.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good workout!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.00,0:06:58.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this early for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.33,0:07:00.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been known to come \Nin early sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:03.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that they located A-drei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.46,0:07:04.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I heard, I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.80,0:07:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said his injuries \Nweren't very severe, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.55,0:07:07.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's good to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.97,0:07:10.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That guy has the devil's own luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For former royalty, he's \Ngot a knack for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.10,0:07:15.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Survival, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.39,0:07:17.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You, on the other hand, don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.85,0:07:20.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it who forced me to survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.83,0:07:21.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.77,0:07:23.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That incident 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.19,0:07:27.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.74,0:07:30.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was the first time I'd ever felt
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.31,0:07:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,death breathing down my neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.24,0:07:34.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Man, what a disaster that was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.45,0:07:36.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We were sent out to eliminate \Na terrorist group,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.40,0:07:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you'd only equipped \Nus with handguns.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.41,0:07:41.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're the one who rushed \Nout ahead of us without
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.71,0:07:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a proper weapon, H-neun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.42,0:07:45.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My intent was to be meticulous \Nin my preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.96,0:07:47.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Was it, now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.63,0:07:50.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're the who says crazy things \Nabout not going by the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.84,0:07:54.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were a bookworm then, \Nand you're a bookworm now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.10,0:07:56.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You probably just took \Ntoo long to get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.47,0:07:59.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You instantly forget things when \Nit's in your best interest to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.18,0:08:00.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.77,0:08:02.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We came this close to dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.81,0:08:05.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we had the \Ndevil's own luck, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.19,0:08:09.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong. What saved \Nus was Captain Cain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.57,0:08:15.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The words he said to us that \Nday still echo deep inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.74,0:08:17.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's such an amazing man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:20.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.04,0:08:23.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to make \Nthe afternoon meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.42,0:08:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Write up a report for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.54,0:08:26.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have something more important to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.92,0:08:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Captain wants to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.96,0:08:32.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm being sent to a manor \Nin the Grünau district.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.72,0:08:33.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Grünau!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.11,0:08:34.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:38.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it, it's nothing. \NWatch your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.98,0:08:41.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What am I, a kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:44.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Grünau...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.24,0:08:52.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoko, no, everyone, is counting on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.24,0:08:59.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have to find Miss \NRukino, too, but I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.87,0:09:04.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not good. You're the same. Like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.71,0:09:05.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The same how?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.83,0:09:08.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Runes decreasing. Are you body-jacking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.50,0:09:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you are eating them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.17,0:09:12.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will eventually lose \Nmemories. Lose life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.80,0:09:13.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.95,0:09:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's important is that \Nyou answer my question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.26,0:09:19.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are modified JIORans the only \Nones who can pilot the Valvraves?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.89,0:09:21.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Modified?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.14,0:09:23.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I mean Sakimori Academy students.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.77,0:09:25.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.10,0:09:27.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All the others. All \Nof them were no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.02,0:09:29.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Made me feel sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.77,0:09:33.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You won't work, either. \NYou don't look very tasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.32,0:09:39.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}People call it the Castle of No Return.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:43.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's a manor that Cain visits \Nregularly when he's off duty.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.71,0:09:46.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As I recall, it's located \Nin the Grünau district...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.69,0:09:50.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought. I'm \Nglad I heard you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:55.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's a constant stream of \Nbizarre rumors about the place.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.43,0:09:57.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even its name comes from the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.07,0:09:59.43,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,people who are brought \Nthere are never seen again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.43,0:10:01.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's that dangerous, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.47,0:10:04.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd love to look into it, but I have \Nmore pressing matters at the moment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.10,0:10:08.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, could you give \Nme the exact location?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.19,0:10:10.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We have plans in motion. \NDon't do anything stupid.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.94,0:10:12.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Relax, it's not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.94,0:10:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to get my hands \Non some juicy intel,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.49,0:10:18.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so I want to memorize potentially \Nimportant keywords.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.83,0:10:30.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it's a good idea \Nto bench two of us pilots?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.75,0:10:33.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps not, but you are the best \Nchoice to search for Saki Rukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.59,0:10:36.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your hand-to-hand combat abilities \Nare second only to my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.76,0:10:38.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And hacking will prove \Nuseful in the search.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.76,0:10:40.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You win.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.26,0:10:43.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, you're the only one other \Nthan me who can recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rukino in her jacked body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.00,0:10:46.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Akira!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.73,0:10:49.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, don't drink any unboiled water. \NAnd do you have your cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.48,0:10:50.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.77,0:10:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you don't \Nwant me to stay behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.90,0:10:55.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You will be working with me \Nindependently. On an operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.49,0:10:57.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Otamaya! Prep all the Valvraves \Nso that they can be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:10:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,powered up at a moment's notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.97,0:11:19.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Phantom, a ship that doesn't \Nexist in Dorssian records,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.22,0:11:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and whose intended use is unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:24.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Royalists lack the equipment \Nto track anything in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.81,0:11:27.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why they \Nneeded our help, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.68,0:11:30.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we can find out which waterway it \Nis using, tracking it will be simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.84,0:11:33.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The people behind the scenes \Nhave let their guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.32,0:11:35.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that the emblem of?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.61,0:11:37.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.08,0:11:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a crest that doesn't belong to \Nthe military or the royal family.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.59,0:12:00.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to expose you for \Nwhat you really are....
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.59,0:12:02.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Cain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.93,0:12:06.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stolen transport located.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.65,0:12:08.95,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,All soldiers on guard \Nduty, assemble at once.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.52,0:12:11.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I repeat, stolen transport \Nhas been located.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.23,0:12:14.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All soldiers on guard \Nduty, assemble at once.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.19,0:12:17.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.82,0:12:20.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That will thin out the \Ncastle's security.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.18,0:12:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be using you to my \Nadvantage, my good students...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.09,0:12:42.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We will need another impact \Nbooster up ahead, eh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.30,0:12:48.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Another crest here...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.31,0:12:59.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}X, I know that you worship the \Nground that Captain Cain walks on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.28,0:13:04.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know that you have no \Nintention of listening to me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.49,0:13:07.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But even so, I want to tell you this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.74,0:13:10.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I saw something.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.25,0:13:13.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I saw him do something that \Nno ordinary person could do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.29,0:13:18.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's when I was certain— \Nthat the Captain isn't human.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.25,0:13:19.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,H-neun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.30,0:13:22.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought, you really do \Nhave a keen sense of smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.93,0:13:26.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if this mission was so important,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you shouldn't have tried \Nto carry it out alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.97,0:13:34.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I was invited to come \Nhere, but I arrived early.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.48,0:13:37.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.06,0:13:40.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's unusual, for someone \Nas constantly tardy as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.94,0:13:43.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.78,0:13:48.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's crucial to have
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.21,0:13:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,someone you can trust watching \Nyour back at all times, H-neun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.71,0:13:55.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's an out of character \Nthing for you to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.58,0:14:02.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That day you saved us 12 years \Nago, you said something to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.35,0:14:14.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:16.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.73,0:14:19.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Never ask a friend to watch your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.11,0:14:22.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have the strength to defend both \Nyour own back and your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.99,0:14:24.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.11,0:14:28.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yet here you are, saying \Nthe exact opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.07,0:14:30.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,X-eins would cry if he heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.50,0:14:38.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see, so this man said \Nsomething like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.00,0:14:40.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"This man"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.22,0:14:48.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've gone and damaged my collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.93,0:14:53.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We've identified the control room, \Nengine room, and auxiliary power room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:57.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, this one hatch isn't \Non the ship's schematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.60,0:14:58.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's behind it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.70,0:15:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll know when we open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.42,0:15:24.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chancellor? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:26.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's your squad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.36,0:15:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you met with Cain?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.47,0:15:30.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's my squad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.10,0:15:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This uniform says I'm from Karlstein!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.35,0:15:33.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Karlstein?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.93,0:15:35.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.47,0:15:36.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need to answer you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.56,0:15:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about the ritual? \NHaven't you started yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.61,0:15:44.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It talked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.02,0:15:46.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this part of the entertainment, Cain?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.32,0:15:50.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, please pardon his poor manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.82,0:15:53.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do show some restraint, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.16,0:15:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight is a rather important ritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.54,0:16:02.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.30,0:16:10.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This light is the same as \Nthe Valvraves and Pino.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.13,0:16:12.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it, \Nthey're harvesting Runes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.80,0:16:14.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does this mean that Runes weren't
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.51,0:16:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a theory that JIOR \Ndiscovered independently?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.93,0:16:20.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dorssia wants Runes, too... So why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.48,0:16:24.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Although acquiring the \Nenormous quantity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.55,0:16:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of Runes needed for the \Nritual was no easy task,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.86,0:16:30.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that ship has served us well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:33.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Another large shipment \Nwill arrive today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.57,0:16:37.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cain. Surely this isn't the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.62,0:16:40.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe I requested \Na young intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.96,0:16:43.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, sir, I'm aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.37,0:16:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The young flesh I have arranged \Nfor you will arrive here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.84,0:16:50.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.30,0:16:52.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rejoice, H-neun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.48,0:16:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X-eins' flesh will soon \Nbelong to my comrade.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.39,0:16:59.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.31,0:17:02.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's time for a \Ngun salute, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.07,0:17:17.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.26,0:17:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With simply averting \Nyour eyes from reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.12,0:17:21.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.41,0:17:23.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't change the \Nfact that Dorssia is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.50,0:17:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,harvesting Runes for \Nsome goal of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.96,0:17:29.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Destroying this ship will only create \Na Phantom II and a Phantom III.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.92,0:17:33.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying it would \Nonly cause more casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.30,0:17:35.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are free to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.41,0:17:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the world will continue \Nturning, unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.64,0:17:41.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you expect me to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.06,0:17:46.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These tremors... Cannon fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.69,0:17:53.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought this location \Nwas supposed to be safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.19,0:17:54.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.07,0:17:58.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Opening right rear hatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.70,0:17:59.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unit 5, launching!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.79,0:18:07.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll block the cannon fire for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.07,0:18:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satomi, take up position behind me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.80,0:18:13.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can't you swat them down?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.01,0:18:14.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All these at once?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.92,0:18:17.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have to head back. \NI can use Unit 1 too
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.68,0:18:19.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That won't be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.55,0:18:21.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Satomi Renbokoji! Do you read me?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.51,0:18:23.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,L-elf? I read you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.91,0:18:26.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Haruto Tokishima is injured. \NI want you to pilot Unit 1.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.98,0:18:28.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tokishima's hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.98,0:18:29.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's the matter?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.90,0:18:31.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you going to sit there trembling,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.41,0:18:33.16,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,waiting for your dear \Nlittle sister to return?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.94,0:18:36.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! L-elf! L-elf!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.91,0:18:38.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.07,0:18:39.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.41,0:18:41.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Every student at that academy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.01,0:18:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ought to have the aptitude \Nto pilot a Valvrave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.80,0:18:45.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.41,0:18:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Getting into it will turn him into a—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.92,0:18:51.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He won't die right away. You \Nare walking proof of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.54,0:18:53.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have plenty of pawns.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.25,0:18:54.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I set up a rotation among
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.69,0:18:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the students to share \NUnit 1 piloting duties,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.76,0:19:01.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we won't have to worry about one \Npilot suffering from Rune deficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.39,0:19:03.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the birth of an \Nunkillable fighting force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.64,0:19:05.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you kidding me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.43,0:19:07.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You knew all this would \Nhappen, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.44,0:19:10.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you got me and Yamada \Naway from the transport!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.44,0:19:11.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.70,0:19:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're no longer a viable combatant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.82,0:19:14.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.82,0:19:16.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the luxury \Nof entrusting Unit 1
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.84,0:19:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to a coward who can't \Nbring himself to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.29,0:19:28.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't... You don't \Nknow what it's like!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.58,0:19:31.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know how it \Nfeels to know that you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.34,0:19:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,might lose your memories \Nand then your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.09,0:19:35.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then do you know what it's like for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.13,0:19:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be unable to wield this power?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.88,0:19:41.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I only had a Valvrave, I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.73,0:19:52.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My heat's almost maxed out!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.78,0:20:02.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.30,0:20:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I turn a blind eye and run \Naway, the world won't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.62,0:20:11.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, I—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.46,0:20:17.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, if this keeps up...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.80,0:20:25.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's running?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.43,0:20:27.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haruto! Where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.72,0:20:28.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's the right move.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.14,0:20:33.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Another 50, 40, 30, 20...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.77,0:20:34.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.03,0:20:42.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The bedrock in this area \Nwas severely softened
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.79,0:20:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by the use of the Harakiri \NBlade in the last battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.58,0:20:48.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, an existing volcano \Nwith high magma content,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.45,0:20:51.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the groundwater temperature, \Nthe impact on the terrain;
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.46,0:20:53.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the conclusion these \Nfactors lead me to is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.15,0:21:21.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't hand it over to anyone. \NI won't share it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.19,0:21:23.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This curse belongs to no one but me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.28,0:21:24.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourself, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.74,0:21:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to use you until you burn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.58,0:21:31.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if I burn out. \NBefore my body falls apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.45,0:21:32.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.55,0:21:41.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...going to put an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:42.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to this war!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.48,0:22:03.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Captain! Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.82,0:22:05.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The volcanic eruption is enough to—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.08,0:22:11.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world happened in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.12,0:22:16.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't... that H-neun's?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.42,0:22:20.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do feel terrible about him, X-eins.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.84,0:22:24.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir? What you do mean?
